G = nx.Graph()
usernames = set()
hashtags = set()
i = 0
for tweet in tags:
    # Get username
    username = twittersubset['username'][i]
    i += 1
    # Process and format hashtags
    hts = [h.lower() for h in tweet]
    
    # Create edges
    for h in hts:
        G.add_edge(username, h)
        usernames.add(username)
        hashtags.add(h)

from itertools import combinations

def node_in_open_triangle(G, n):
    in_open_triangle = False
    for n1, n2 in combinations(G.neighbors(n), 2):
        if not G.has_edge(n1, n2):
            in_open_triangle = True
            print([n, n1, n2])
            break
    return in_open_triangle

nltk.download('stopwords')
nltk.download('vader_lexicon')
nltk.download('wordnet')

# Preprocess tweets
stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
sid = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()

preprocessed_tweets = []

for tweet in twitter['full_text']:
    # Remove URLs, mentions, and hashtags
    text = ' '.join(word for word in tweet.split())
    # Remove punctuation and convert to lowercase
    text = ''.join(char for char in text if char.isalnum() or char.isspace())
    text = text.lower()
    # Tokenize text and remove stop words
    words = nltk.word_tokenize(text)
    words = [word for word in words if word not in stop_words]
    # Lemmatize words
    words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in words]
    # Calculate sentiment score
    sentiment_score = sid.polarity_scores(text)['compound']
    # Add preprocessed tweet to list
    preprocessed_tweets.append({'text': text, 'words': words, 'sentiment': sentiment_score})

from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

# Vectorize preprocessed tweets
vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()
vectorized_tweets = vectorizer.fit_transform(tweet['text'] for tweet in preprocessed_tweets)

# Cluster tweets using K-means
num_clusters = 15
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=num_clusters)
kmeans.fit(vectorized_tweets)
print(kmeans.inertia_)

# Assign cluster labels to preprocessed tweets
for i, tweet in enumerate(preprocessed_tweets):
    tweet['cluster'] = kmeans.labels_[i]

# Print sentiment and topic analysis
for cluster in range(num_clusters):
    cluster_tweets = [tweet for tweet in preprocessed_tweets if tweet['cluster'] == cluster]
    num_tweets = len(cluster_tweets)
    avg_sentiment = sum(tweet['sentiment'] for tweet in cluster_tweets) / num_tweets
    print(f'Cluster {cluster}: {num_tweets} tweets, average sentiment = {avg_sentiment:.2f}')

    sum_of_squared_distances = []
    K=range(1,11) # change 8 in your data 
    for k in K:
        km=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
        km=km.fit(vectorized_tweets)
        sum_of_squared_distances.append(km.inertia_)
    plt.plot(K, sum_of_squared_distances, 'bx-')
    plt.xlabel('k')
    plt.ylabel('sum_of_squared_distances')
    plt.title('Elbow method for optimal k')
    plt.show()

# Sort by favorite and filter out columns to lower memory requirements
test = twitter.sort_values('favorite_count', ascending=False)[:10000]

# Preprocess tweets
stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()

cleaned = []

for tweet in test['full_text']:
    # Remove URLs, mentions, and hashtags
    text = ' '.join(word for word in tweet.split())
    # Remove punctuation and convert to lowercase
    text = ''.join(char for char in text if char.isalnum() or char.isspace())
    text = text.lower()
    # Tokenize text and remove stop words
    words = nltk.word_tokenize(text)
    words = [word for word in words if word not in stop_words]
    # Lemmatize words
    words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in words]
    # Add preprocessed tweet to list
    cleaned.append({'text': text, 'words': words})

from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer

def vectorize(data,tfidf_vect_fit):
    X_tfidf = tfidf_vect_fit.transform(data)
    words = tfidf_vect_fit.get_feature_names_out()
    X_tfidf_df = pd.DataFrame(X_tfidf.toarray())
    X_tfidf_df.columns = words
    return(X_tfidf_df)
